## `<file-level: imports>`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-fs-1 -->

### Purpose
The `Filesystem` class â€” the orchestrator. Owns one `sqlite3.Connection`, a `FdTable`, a `LockManager`, and a `(uid, gid)` identity. Composes primitives from every storage module and enforces permissions.

### Implementation Notes

```python
import os
import sqlite3
import time
from contextlib import contextmanager

from sqlite_fs import (
    blobs,
    entries,
    nodes,
    xattrs as xattrs_mod,
    symlinks as symlinks_mod,
)
from sqlite_fs.errors import (
    AlreadyExists,
    BadFileDescriptor,
    DirectoryNotEmpty,
    FilesystemError,
    InvalidArgument,
    IsADirectory,
    NotADirectory,
    NotFound,
    PermissionDenied,
    ReadOnlyFilesystem,
    SymlinkLoop,
)
from sqlite_fs.fdtable import FdTable
from sqlite_fs.locks import LockManager
from sqlite_fs.paths import parse_path
from sqlite_fs.perms import require_access, Access, check_access
from sqlite_fs.schema import (
    MAXSYMLINKS,
    ROOT_INODE,
    apply_pragmas,
    load_chunk_size,
)
from sqlite_fs.types import (
    DirEntry,
    FlockOp,
    LockOp,
    LockQuery,
    Stat,
)

ROOT_PARENT = None    # sentinel for root's parent column
```

